Sallie Hart Williams,

	Creative Director

Sallie Williams joined the Altavista team in 2013 to help with client service, office management, and administrative projects as needed. As Creative Director she also manages social media, communications, leads the marketing team and acts as event coordinator for the firm.

	 

Sallie earned an interdisciplinary degree from the University of the South: Sewanee. After graduation in 2006, she traveled to Bangladesh to study the microfinance model of Dr. Yunus at Grameen Bank, when he received the Nobel Peace Prize. Sallie worked in the finance and non-profit arena from 2007 to 2013 including positions with The Episcopal Diocese of WNC and OnTrack Financial Education & Counseling. She also served a year as an AmeriCorps Volunteer with Knoxville Habitat for Humanity.


“We stand ready to work closely and enthusiastically with our clients.” 


Sallie and her husband, Ian have two young children, Nora and Greyson. They enjoy sharing meals with friends and family on their porch and exploring the outdoors with their dog, Bay. They are members of St. Luke's Episcopal Church on Chunns Cove.

	 

