Logan Bolick, CFA

	Director of Research, Financial Advisor



	Logan joined Altavista in 2013.  Logan believes in a comprehensive approach to financial advice that establishes investments and financial planning as means to accomplish client goals.  As Director of Research, Logan coordinates the Altavista Investment Committee, conducts investment analysis, compiles economic research and assesses financial market conditions. 

	 

	In addition, Logan implements the firm’s Investment Committee recommendations through trading strategies and rebalancing.  He also manages Altavista’s client reporting framework.  Logan is a CFA® charterholder and a member of the CFA Society of North Carolina.

	 

	Logan is a graduate of the Kenan-Flagler Undergraduate Business School at UNC-Chapel Hill.  He emphasized in finance while earning his Bachelor of Science in Business Administration.  As a student, Logan served as president of Kenan-Flagler’s Undergraduate Finance Club.  He is also an Eagle Scout.

	 

	It is common to find Logan up early on a Saturday morning to enjoy an English Premiere League match and a cup of coffee before a bike ride on the roads around Asheville.  He and his wife Sarah, a teacher and coach, enjoy travelling and spending time with family and friends.

	“Our primary concern is to help our clients achieve their financial goals.”

